What you need to know:  Ironically coached by a Russian (Tetyana Stepanova), Mahuchikh became Ukraine’s first global sports champion of the “war era” when she bagged the World Indoor Championships’ gold medal at a rapturous Štark Arena here on Saturday.Mahuchikh’s compatriot Iryna Gerashchenko finished fifth with a jump of 1.92 metres behind Marija Vukovic (1.95m) of Montenegro.